# The deployed app is fully static (index.html + static/ run in the browser).
# Everything below is Python pipeline / training tooling and datasets that the
# site does not need at runtime — keeping them out also stops Vercel from
# mis-detecting this as a Flask backend.
*.py
*.pt
pipeline/
tools/
requirements-dev.txt
# anchored: exclude the top-level Python models/ but KEEP static/models/ (the
# site's ONNX detectors) — an unanchored "models/" would strip those and break it
/models/
normal_frame/
ray_ban_frame/
ray_ban_face/
normal_glassess/
actual_rayban_cases/
data/
.venv-train/
debug/
view/
browser_test.html
README.md
